	(20,'Algolia','How Algolia (YC W14) Built Their Realtime Search',60,'Why do you think consumer disks are better for a search engine?Everything is a balance between CPU/RAM/Disk. Having one of this resource that is far superior than the other would be a waste of resource. Our balance is globally to have about 16 cores/32threads per host with latest XEON >= 3.5Ghz, 256G of RAM and about 1TB of SSD (2X512G)We perform a lot of IO, so the compromise is between price and number of IOPS we can get. Having the same IOPS than our two SSD in raid0, would require a lot of consumer disk, which leads to two problems:\\n 1) We would have too many disk space and we will not have enough CPU to use all this space\\n 2) It would not fit in a 1U server and would increase a lot the price of the server',1.00,2,'Operating','Algolia provides a developer-friendly search API enabling users to perform database search functions in a user-friendly manner.','2014','Winter',2800000.00,'San Francisco','http://a5.images.crunchbase.com/image/upload/c_pad,h_98,w_98/v1397183785/3110baf2d02da512dfee7fb0ed267d36.png','http://www.seed-db.com/companies/view?companyid=5631383682678784','http://www.crunchbase.com/organization/algolia','http://www.algolia.com','Operating',0.767,'Alven Capital, Point Nine Capital, Index Ventures, Y Combinator','Julien Lemoine','Search, Software','https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=7456827'),
