	(65,'1000Memories','NYTimes on Facebook death, and why we created 1000Memories (YC S10)',83,'Cemeteries have endowment funds to ensure the land where people are buried will remain land where people are buried.  Sites like this have nothing of the sort. I don\'t even see a business model.Without something to guarantee people\'s memories will live long in the site, you run the risk of their loved ones being taken from them twice. You didn\'t even address this point on the first page, instead just start talking about your nifty features.You really need to think about how your startup is going to avoid death if you are asking people to put their faith in you when they try to preserve memories of their loved ones.',0.80,20,'Operating','1000Memories is an online portal that lets people organize share and discover old photos and memories and set up family trees.','2010','Summer',2515000.00,'San Francisco','http://a4.images.crunchbase.com/image/upload/c_pad,h_98,w_98/v1397186310/a174ac407cbd537e892781705d76cb38.jpg','http://www.seed-db.com/companies/view?companyid=94018','http://www.crunchbase.com/organization/1000memories','http://1000memories.com','Operating',0.567,'FLOODGATE, Keith Rabois, Paul Buchheit, Felicis Ventures, Chris Sacca, Ron Conway, Greylock Partners, Caterina Fake, Y Combinator','Brett Huneycutt, Jonathan Good, Rudy Adler','Curated Web','https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=1526833'),
