	(83,'AeroFS','AeroFS (YC S10) exits private beta',144,'This is awesome.  AeroFS does everything I want in a file sharing system -- I can either run it entirely on my own machines on LAN and potentially VPN, or at a company on a network also not connected to the Internet, or I can use it as a direct Dropbox alternative (although it lacks some mobile clients and API support).I\'ve been using it for ~a year or two in beta, as well as all the other alternatives.  I still use Dropbox for interoperating with other people who use Dropbox, and for a couple mobile devices which don\'t support anything else, and I use iCloud for mainly Apple app sync (although it seems to suck for most non-Apple apps) between OSX and iOS, but AeroFS is my preferred option for general file sharing use.The only downside I\'ve found is dealing with Java on certain OSes (OSX and Windows 7 at times), but generally OS-level Java is fine, it\'s browser Java which sucks.',0.25,15,'Operating','AeroFS provides a file sharing and syncing service that does not require the user\'s files be loaded or stored on third party servers.','2010','Summer',17000.00,'Palo Alto','http://a4.images.crunchbase.com/image/upload/c_pad,h_98,w_98/v1397194385/575d26dac80d66f62e8e7932652896c9.jpg','http://www.seed-db.com/companies/view?companyid=103021','http://www.crunchbase.com/organization/aerofs','http://www.aerofs.com','Not Operating',0.700,'Geoff Ralston, Andreessen Horowitz, Ashton Kutcher, Chris Sacca, Webb Investment Network, Ash Patel, Naval Ravikant, AME Cloud Ventures, Paul Buchheit, SV Angel, Webb Investment Network, Y Combinator','Weihan Wang, Yuri Sagalov','Cloud Computing, Storage, Enterprise Software','https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=5483600'),
	(84,'Circuithub','CircuitHub (YC W12) Aims To Be A One-Stop Shop For Electrical Parts',89,'When they say \"shop\", I thought it was going to be a specialized store for buying parts.In fact, it seems to be more focused on becoming some kind of cross-application database of parts information, storing data sheets and CAD models for use in schematics design. Their own description includes the word \"library\", which is more descriptive. I guess I\'m (as a non-native speaker) is intepreting the term \"one stop shop\" too literally, when the context seems to allow it.At least that\'s what I think, so far. Also, the only way to \"log in\" seems to be to connect my Dropbox account to their site, which I found odd.Also, since they promise free access, I\'m not at all sure about the business model here. Of course, lots of other people seem to be so I\'m sure it\'s fine. :)',0.75,9,'Operating','AWS For Manufacturing - We scale hardware companies from prototype to production.','2012','Winter',17000.00,'San Jose','http://a1.images.crunchbase.com/image/upload/c_pad,h_98,w_98/v1397196054/cd4793ce82f7a1336fd4864e7819fdb9.png','http://www.seed-db.com/companies/view?companyid=94024','http://www.crunchbase.com/organization/circuithub','http://circuithub.com','Not Operating',0.767,'Google Ventures, Alexis Ohanian, Y Combinator','Andrew Seddon, Jon Friedman, Rehno Lindeque','Manufacturing','https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=5109124'),
