	(229,'Can\'tWait','IPhone App Helps You Discover Upcoming Movies (YCS11)',45,'I\'m worried about the apparent disconnect between my brain and the world of web startups or maybe even simply the world. I think YC numbers are proof enough that startups like this can become popular and commercial successes.Yet as someone who likes movies and watches a lot of them it\'s completely beyond me how something like this could ever be more than a minor feature of some movie site, one that is trivial to copy for anyone in the space with the advantage of an existing user base.I have no reason whatsoever to trash this startup, quite the contrary, I\'m in a completely different space and I wish only the best to any and all fellow startup founders. I\'m just honestly puzzled, fully aware that it\'s probably me who is going to be wrong again.I\'m just wondering if anyone else is struggling to convince themselves to take something as simple as this and run with it in a crowded market. Even if I had the slightest interest in solving this problem, I just couldn\'t bring myself to believe in it and that might be why I will very likely never strike it rich.',0.39,11,'Operating','Be the first to hear about movies that you will love!','2011','Summer',17000.00,'','http://a4.images.crunchbase.com/image/upload/c_pad,h_98,w_98/v1397193662/129c3a8d3162b625cc0942cb1f668d11.jpg','http://www.seed-db.com/companies/view?companyid=92032','http://www.crunchbase.com/organization/cantwait','','Not Operating',0.978,'Y Combinator','','','https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=2952984'),
