	(465,'Wundrbar','Wundrbar is the next generation of search (YC Winter 08)',48,'One thing people don\'t want to do is have to memorize a syntax just to use a search engine.  A lot of people have trouble with Google as it is.  I realize that the idea is to augment traditional search engines\' capabilities (so that people will have less trouble), but it\'s going to have to be easy for non-hackers to catch on to it.  The learning curve has to be shallow or the average user is going to give up on it.  That being said I really like the way it tells you what it thinks you mean as you type though, and definitely think there is potential for this type of thing.',0.50,10,'Dead','Wundrbar wants to improve upon the search bar experience by providing users with powerful inline commands.','2008','Winter',17000.00,'San Francisco','http://a2.images.crunchbase.com/image/upload/c_pad,h_98,w_98/v1397184741/14c6ebdd31c6b3cda70b4f016fc0991a.png','http://www.seed-db.com/companies/view?companyid=100011','http://www.crunchbase.com/organization/wundrbar','http://wundrbar.com','Not Operating',0.933,'Y Combinator','Andrew Dudley, Nick Grandy','Search','https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=137226'),
